Build Order & Sprint Plan – Java Backend MVP

Purpose

This document defines a practical build order and sprint plan to implement the Java backend MVP using all locked specifications.

Goals:
	•	Reduce integration risk
	•	Deliver vertical slices that are testable early
	•	Avoid rework by respecting locked boundaries

Assumption:
	•	1–2 backend developers
	•	Monolith-first, modular structure
	•	Frontend (Astro + Admin SPA) can start in parallel once Public/Admin APIs are available

⸻

Sprint 0 – Project & Infrastructure Setup (Foundation)

Objective: Get the project runnable with guardrails.

Deliverables
	•	Spring Boot project skeleton
	•	Module folder structure:
	•	auth
	•	tenancy
	•	store
	•	orders
	•	payments
	•	content-gateway
	•	observability
	•	events
	•	Liquibase configured
	•	Initial empty changelog folders per module
	•	Neon Postgres connection via Hikari
	•	Environment profiles: dev, prod

Key tasks
	•	Configure Liquibase with SQL changelogs
	•	Configure logging (JSON + MDC placeholders)
	•	Implement request filter:
	•	traceId
	•	MDC wiring
	•	Health endpoint /actuator/health

Exit criteria
	•	App starts locally
	•	Liquibase runs clean
	•	Logs include traceId

⸻

Sprint 1 – Auth, Tenant, Membership (Critical Path)

Objective: Secure access + tenant isolation.

Deliverables
	•	User, tenant, membership schema
	•	Auth flows:
	•	login
	•	tenant selection
	•	refresh (rotation)
	•	logout
	•	switch tenant
	•	Invite-by-link
	•	Password reset-by-link
	•	Centralized authorization policy wired

Key tasks
	•	Implement TenantContext
	•	JWT parsing & generation
	•	Refresh token storage & rotation
	•	Membership status enforcement
	•	Integration tests:
	•	tenant isolation
	•	refresh reuse detection

Exit criteria
	•	Can log in, select tenant, refresh token
	•	Disabled membership blocks access immediately

⸻

Sprint 2 – Store Module (Catalog Core)

Objective: Products, categories, images, linked products.

Deliverables
	•	Store DB schema (products, categories, images, linked products)
	•	CRUD APIs for:
	•	categories
	•	products
	•	product images (R2)
	•	linked products (pseudo-variants)
	•	SKU generation service
	•	CAP_STORE gating

Key tasks
	•	Implement tenant-scoped repositories
	•	Implement R2 upload + metadata persistence
	•	Validate primary-category constraint for linked products
	•	Integration tests:
	•	SKU uniqueness
	•	tenant isolation

Exit criteria
	•	Admin can fully manage catalog
	•	Images upload and display via public URLs

⸻

Sprint 3 – Public Catalog APIs (Astro dependency)

Objective: Read-only catalog for storefront.

Deliverables
	•	Public endpoints:
	•	categories
	•	product list
	•	product detail (with images + linked products)
	•	Host-based tenant resolution
	•	Pagination, filtering, sorting
	•	Cache hooks (optional)

Key tasks
	•	Implement Host → tenant resolver
	•	DTO mappers for public responses
	•	Rate limiting on catalog endpoints (light)

Exit criteria
	•	Astro can render shop pages from API

⸻

Sprint 4 – Orders Core (Offline-first)

Objective: Order lifecycle without PSP.

Deliverables
	•	Orders + order_items schema
	•	Public checkout create order
	•	Merchant Admin order list + detail
	•	Fulfillment lifecycle:
	•	NEW → CONFIRMED → FULFILLING → READY → COMPLETED
	•	Offline payment marking

Key tasks
	•	Enforce fulfillment/payment gating rules
	•	Snapshot product data into order_items
	•	Audit events for order changes
	•	Integration tests:
	•	state transitions
	•	offline payment flow

Exit criteria
	•	Full offline selling flow works

⸻

Sprint 5 – Payments Abstraction + Wompi

Objective: Online payments for Pro-ready tenants.

Deliverables
	•	PaymentProvider abstraction
	•	PaymentAttempt lifecycle
	•	Wompi provider implementation
	•	Webhook endpoint + signature verification
	•	Idempotency

Key tasks
	•	Secret management for tenant PSP keys
	•	Async webhook processing
	•	Reconciliation edge cases
	•	Integration tests with Wompi sandbox

Exit criteria
	•	Orders can be paid via Wompi
	•	Webhook retries safe and idempotent

⸻

Sprint 6 – Content Gateway (Payload Integration)

Objective: Site editing via Merchant Admin.

Deliverables
	•	Content Gateway module
	•	Payload client integration
	•	Site settings endpoints
	•	Page edit endpoints
	•	Audit logging for content changes

Key tasks
	•	Allowlist field mapping
	•	TenantId enforcement
	•	Cache invalidation hooks

Exit criteria
	•	Admin can edit site without accessing Payload

⸻

Sprint 7 – Observability, Hardening & Polish

Objective: Production readiness.

Deliverables
	•	Metrics dashboards
	•	Alerts (checkout, payment failures)
	•	Rate limiting hardened
	•	Dead-letter handling for webhooks

Key tasks
	•	Grafana dashboards
	•	Alert tuning
	•	Load testing checkout endpoints

Exit criteria
	•	System observable under load

⸻

Parallel Work (Can overlap sprints)
	•	Frontend Admin SPA development once Sprint 1 APIs stabilize
	•	Astro storefront once Sprint 3 APIs stabilize
	•	Documentation & runbooks

⸻

Final Notes
	•	Scheduling and Domain Management are intentionally deferred
	•	Each sprint delivers a vertical slice
	•	Avoid starting Wompi before offline orders are stable

This plan is locked, realistic, and execution-focused.